Sentencas: Ni-YSZ cermet anode supports solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) were fabricated by high-frequency induction heated sintering (HFIHS) under 60 MPa pressure with powders synthesized by the glycine nitrate process (GNP) as well as mechanically mixed commercial powders.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of a Ni-YSZ anode support using high-frequency induction heated sintering (HFIHS)

Sentencas: The HFIHS method created a uniformly porous microstructure without abnormal grain growth compared to the conventional sintering method.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of a Ni-YSZ anode support using high-frequency induction heated sintering (HFIHS)

Sentencas: Samples sintered by HFIHS show higher strength and electrical conductivity than conventionally sintered samples, even though they have similar porosity.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of a Ni-YSZ anode support using high-frequency induction heated sintering (HFIHS)
